## Context
The test suite works but has gaps in strategy: no regression guards
on numeric values, no fast/slow separation, and several scripts lack
any test coverage.

## Actions

### Golden value regression tests
1. Run all 15 methods on smoke fixture, save outputs to
   `tests/fixtures/smoke/golden/tab_div_*.csv`.
2. Add `test_golden_values.py`: for each method, compare output
   against golden values with `np.allclose(atol=1e-6)`.
3. Golden values are committed to git. Update when methods change
   intentionally (not silently).

### Fast/slow test split
4. Mark all subprocess-spawning smoke tests with `@pytest.mark.slow`.
5. Mark all tests that do real computation (S1-S4 on fixture) with
   `@pytest.mark.slow`.
6. Unit tests (schema, helpers, synthetic data) stay unmarked.
7. Verify: `pytest -m "not slow"` < 10 seconds.
8. Document: `make check-fast` runs `pytest -m "not slow"`,
   `make check` runs all.

### Missing test coverage
9. `plot_convergence.py` — smoke test: produces PNG without error.
10. `compute_convergence.py` (script) — smoke test via subprocess.
11. `_get_break_years` with realistic breaks DataFrame — unit test
    verifying both `detector_params` and legacy `penalty` formats.
12. Property tests for S1-S4: distance(X, X) ≈ 0, distance(X, Y) ≥ 0.

### Makefile test target
13. Add `make check-divergence` target running only divergence tests.
14. Add `make -n divergence` dry-run test verifying DAG integrity.

## Test
`pytest -m "not slow"` completes in < 10 seconds.
`pytest` (all) completes in < 150 seconds.

## Exit criteria
Golden values committed. Fast/slow split working. All scripts have
at least one test. Property tests for metric axioms.

